{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863134719,"sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","part":{"id":"prt_d79b0edfe001sIMXOeLn8uj8Ax","messageID":"msg_d79b0d931001NUgSrarJDMgXTq","sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-4b20f80413af4366b907a06b7bcaab05","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Extend PicoD's file management capabilities beyond the basic upload, list, and download operations implemented in AR-015. This adds comprehensive file system manipulation APIs including file deletion, directory creation, file copy/move, permissions modification, and archive operations (tar/zip) for AI agent workspace management.\n6: \n7: **Current State**: PicoD (AR-015) provides basic file operations: `POST /api/files` (upload), `GET /api/files?path=...` (list), `GET /api/files/*path` (download). Missing: deletion, directory creation, copy/move, permissions change, and archive handling.\n8: \n9: **Target State**: Full-featured file management API suite:\n10: - `DELETE /api/files/*path` — Delete files and directories\n11: - `POST /api/files/directory` — Create directories with optional mode\n12: - `POST /api/files/copy` — Copy files/directories within workspace\n13: - `POST /api/files/move` — Move/rename files/directories\n14: - `PATCH /api/files/*path` — Modify file permissions\n15: - `POST /api/files/archive` — Create tar/zip archives\n16: - `POST /api/files/extract` — Extract tar/zip archives\n17: \n18: ## Scope\n19: \n20: ### In Scope\n21: \n22: | Deliverable | Description |\n23: |-------------|-------------|\n24: | `pkg/picod/files.go` (extend) | Add DeleteFileHandler, CreateDirectoryHandler, CopyFileHandler, MoveFileHandler, ModifyPermissionsHandler |\n25: | `pkg/picod/archive.go` | New file: ArchiveHandler, ExtractHandler with tar/zip support |\n26: | `pkg/picod/files.go` structs | DeleteRequest, CreateDirectoryRequest, CopyRequest, MoveRequest, ModifyPermissionsRequest, ArchiveRequest, ExtractRequest |\n27: | `pkg/picod/server.go` (extend) | Register new file management routes |\n28: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` (extend) | Unit tests for all new handlers |\n29: \n30: ### Implementation Details\n31: \n32: #### Request/Response Structures\n33: \n34: **Delete**:\n35: ```go\n36: type DeleteRequest struct {\n37:     Path      string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n38:     Recursive bool   `json:\"recursive\"` // For directory deletion\n39: }\n40: \n41: type DeleteResponse struct {\n42:     Path   string `json:\"path\"`\n43:     Deleted bool  `json:\"deleted\"`\n44: }\n45: ```\n46: \n47: **Create Directory**:\n48: ```go\n49: type CreateDirectoryRequest struct {\n50:     Path string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n51:     Mode string `json:\"mode\"` // Octal, default 0755\n52: }\n53: \n54: type CreateDirectoryResponse struct {\n55:     Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n56:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`\n57:     Created  bool      `json:\"created\"`\n58: }\n59: ```\n60: \n61: **Copy**:\n62: ```go\n63: type CopyRequest struct {\n64:     Source string `json:\"source\" binding:\"required\"`\n65:     Dest   string `json:\"dest\" binding:\"required\"`\n66: }\n67: \n68: type CopyResponse struct {\n69:     Source string `json:\"source\"`\n70:     Dest   string `json:\"dest\"`\n71:     Copied bool   `json:\"copied\"`\n72: }\n73: ```\n74: \n75: **Move**:\n76: ```go\n77: type MoveRequest struct {\n78:     Source string `json:\"source\" binding:\"required\"`\n79:     Dest   string `json:\"dest\" binding:\"required\"`\n80: }\n81: \n82: type MoveResponse struct {\n83:     Source string `json:\"source\"`\n84:     Dest   string `json:\"dest\"`\n85:     Moved  bool   `json:\"moved\"`\n86: }\n87: ```\n88: \n89: **Modify Permissions**:\n90: ```go\n91: type ModifyPermissionsRequest struct {\n92:     Path string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`\n93:     Mode string `json:\"mode\" binding:\"required\"` // Octal\n94: }\n95: \n96: type ModifyPermissionsResponse struct {\n97:     Path     string    `json:\"path\"`\n98:     OldMode  string    `json:\"old_mode\"`\n99:     NewMode  string    `json:\"new_mode\"`\n100: }\n101: ```\n102: \n103: **Archive**:\n104: ```go\n105: type ArchiveRequest struct {\n106:     SourcePath string `json:\"source_path\" binding:\"required\"` // Directory or file to archive\n107:     DestPath   string `json:\"dest_path\" binding:\"required\"`   // Output archive path\n108:     Format     string `json:\"format\"`                         // \"tar\" or \"zip\", default \"tar\"\n109: }\n110: \n111: type ArchiveResponse struct {\n112:     SourcePath string `json:\"source_path\"`\n113:     DestPath   string `json:\"dest_path\"`\n114:     Format     string `json:\"format\"`\n115:     Size       int64  `json:\"size\"`\n116: }\n117: ```\n118: \n119: **Extract**:\n120: ```go\n121: type ExtractRequest struct {\n122:     SourcePath string `json:\"source_path\" binding:\"required\"` // Archive to extract\n123:     DestPath   string `json:\"dest_path\"`                      // Destination directory, defaults to archive parent\n124: }\n125: \n126: type ExtractResponse struct {\n127:     SourcePath string     `json:\"source_path\"`\n128:     DestPath   string     `json:\"dest_path\"`\n129:     Files      []FileEntry `json:\"files\"` // Extracted files list\n130: }\n131: ```\n132: \n133: #### Route Registration Extension\n134: \n135: ```go\n136: api.DELETE(\"/files/*path\", s.DeleteFileHandler)\n137: api.POST(\"/files/directory\", s.CreateDirectoryHandler)\n138: api.POST(\"/files/copy\", s.CopyFileHandler)\n139: api.POST(\"/files/move\", s.MoveFileHandler)\n140: api.PATCH(\"/files/*path\", s.ModifyPermissionsHandler)\n141: api.POST(\"/files/archive\", s.ArchiveHandler)\n142: api.POST(\"/files/extract\", s.ExtractHandler)\n143: ```\n144: \n145: #### Handler Implementations\n146: \n147: | Handler | Logic |\n148: |---------|-------|\n149: | `DeleteFileHandler` | Wildcard path; `os.Stat` to check if file or dir; file: `os.Remove`; dir: `os.RemoveAll` if recursive, else error if non-empty |\n150: | `CreateDirectoryHandler` | JSON bind; sanitize; `parseFileMode`; `os.MkdirAll`; return created status |\n151: | `CopyFileHandler` | Sanitize source/dest; `os.Stat` source; file: `io.Copy`; dir: recursive copy via `filepath.Walk` |\n152: | `MoveFileHandler` | Sanitize source/dest; `os.Rename`; handles cross-directory moves |\n153: | `ModifyPermissionsHandler` | Wildcard path; `os.Chmod` with parsed mode; return old/new mode |\n154: | `ArchiveHandler` | Sanitize paths; `archive/tar` or `archive/zip`; walk source, add entries; write to dest |\n155: | `ExtractHandler` | Sanitize paths; detect format by extension or request field; `tar.NewReader` or `zip.OpenReader`; extract each entry |\n156: \n157: #### Constants\n158: \n159: | Name | Value | Purpose |\n160: |------|-------|---------|\n161: | `defaultDirMode` | `0755` | Default directory creation mode |\n162: | `maxArchiveSize` | `100 << 20` (100 MiB) | Maximum archive size for extraction safety |\n163: | `allowedArchiveFormats` | `[\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\"]` | Supported archive formats |\n164: \n165: ### Out of Scope\n166: \n167: - Symlink creation/resolution API (separate security concerns)\n168: - Multiple workspace roots\n169: - File content search/grep API\n170: - File locking/concurrent access control\n171: - Chunked/streaming large file operations\n172: - Remote file URLs (no external fetch)\n173: - File checksum verification (MD5/SHA)\n174: - Quarantine/sandbox escape detection beyond existing sanitizePath\n175: - Recursive permission modification\n176: - File ownership change (chown)\n177: \n178: ## Impact Analysis\n179: \n180: ### Upstream Dependencies\n181: \n182: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n183: |------------|---------|--------|\n184: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10+ | HTTP framework; existing from AR-015 |\n185: | `archive/tar` | Standard | Tar archive creation/extraction |\n186: | `archive/zip` | Standard | Zip archive creation/extraction |\n187: | `compress/gzip` | Standard | Gzip compression for tar.gz |\n188: | `io` | Standard | Stream copying for file operations |\n189: | `filepath` | Standard | Path walking for recursive operations |\n190: | `os` | Standard | File system operations |\n191: \n192: ### Downstream Consumers\n193: \n194: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n195: |----------|--------------|\n196: | CodeInterpreter Sandbox Pods | Directory creation for output folders; archive extraction for uploaded packages; cleanup via delete |\n197: | Agent Runtime Sandbox Pods | Move/rename for artifact organization; copy for backup; permissions for security staging |\n198: | Python SDK | Full file manipulation API calls; archive handling for dataset uploads |\n199: | Router | No direct impact; JWT auth unchanged |\n200: \n201: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n202: \n203: - **New Routes Only**: All additions are new routes; no existing endpoints modified\n204: - **Backward Compatible**: AR-015 file APIs remain unchanged\n205: - **Behavioral Consistency**: Same sanitizePath security applied to all new operations\n206: - **Archive Format**: Only tar/zip supported; other formats rejected with error\n207: \n208: ### Compatibility Notes\n209: \n210: 1. **Path Security**: All new operations use existing `sanitizePath` for workspace jail enforcement\n211: 2. **Recursive Operations**: Delete/copy with recursive flag; explicit flag prevents accidental mass deletion\n212: 3. **Archive Paths**: Archive extraction validates each entry path against workspace jail\n213: 4. **Move Semantics**: `os.Rename` may fail across filesystem boundaries; error returned if unsupported\n214: 5. **Permissions Octal**: Same `parseFileMode` pattern as upload; octal string input\n215: \n216: ## Alternatives Considered\n217: \n218: ### Alternative 1: Single Multi-Operation Endpoint\n219: \n220: **Approach**: `POST /api/files/operation` with `operation` field specifying copy/move/delete/etc.\n221: \n222: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n223: |--------|------------|\n224: | Pros | Single endpoint; consistent request structure |\n225: | Cons | Less RESTful; harder to document; mixed error handling |\n226: \n227: **Decision**: Rejected. Separate endpoints follow REST conventions, enable granular error handling, and match existing PicoD API style.\n228: \n229: ### Alternative 2: External Archive Tools\n230: \n231: **Approach**: Use `tar`/`zip` CLI commands via `exec.CommandContext` for archive operations.\n232: \n233: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n234: |--------|------------|\n235: | Pros | Leverages well-tested tools; supports all formats |\n236: | Cons | Depends on container having tools installed; security via command execution; less portable |\n237: \n238: **Decision**: Rejected. Native Go `archive/tar` and `archive/zip` libraries are cross-platform, don't require container dependencies, and integrate with existing sanitization logic.\n239: \n240: ### Alternative 3: File Operations via Command Execution\n241: \n242: **Approach**: Users implement file operations via `POST /api/execute` with shell commands (`rm`, `mkdir`, `cp`, `mv`).\n243: \n244: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n245: |--------|------------|\n246: | Pros | No new code; maximum flexibility |\n247: | Cons | Shell-dependent; less secure; no structured error responses; harder to audit |\n248: \n249: **Decision**: Rejected. Dedicated API endpoints provide structured responses, consistent path security, and audit-friendly operation logs.\n250: \n251: ### Alternative 4: WebDAV Protocol\n252: \n253: **Approach**: Expose WebDAV server for file operations (PROPFIND, COPY, MOVE, DELETE).\n254: \n255: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n256: |--------|------------|\n257: | Pros | Standard protocol; existing client libraries; directory listing built-in |\n258: | Cons | Different auth integration; more complex middleware; not JSON-based |\n259: \n260: **Decision**: Rejected. REST/JSON API matches PicoD's existing design and Router integration. WebDAV would require separate auth handling and different middleware stack.\n261: \n262: ### Alternative 5: Batch Operations Endpoint\n263: \n264: **Approach**: `POST /api/files/batch` accepting array of operations in single request.\n265: \n266: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n267: |--------|------------|\n268: | Pros | Reduced round trips; atomic grouping |\n269: | Cons | Complex error handling; partial failure semantics unclear |\n270: \n271: **Decision**: Deferred. Batch operations are valuable but add complexity. Initial implementation uses single-operation endpoints; batch can be added later without breaking changes.\n272: \n273: ## Risks\n274: \n275: | Risk | Mitigation |\n276: |------|------------|\n277: | Recursive delete destroys workspace | `Recursive` flag required for directory deletion; non-empty dir without flag returns error |\n278: | Archive extraction path escape | Validate each archive entry path via `sanitizePath`; reject entries attempting `..` escape |\n279: | Large archive DoS | `maxArchiveSize` = 100 MiB; reject archives exceeding limit; streaming extraction avoids memory exhaustion |\n280: | Copy infinite loop (circular symlink) | `sanitizePath` resolves symlinks; skip symlinks in recursive copy or resolve target first |\n281: | Move across filesystem boundaries | `os.Rename` returns specific error; handler detects and returns appropriate message |\n282: | Concurrent modification conflict | No locking; operations are atomic at OS level; last-write-wins semantics |\n283: | Permission change security | Mode limited to `<= 0777`; same `parseFileMode` validation as upload |\n284: | Archive format confusion | Detect format by file extension + request field; reject unsupported formats |\n285: \n286: ## Implementation Checklist\n287: \n288: 1. **Delete Handler**\n289:    - Wildcard path extraction\n290:    - `os.Stat` to determine type\n291:    - File: `os.Remove`\n292:    - Directory: check `recursive` flag; `os.RemoveAll` or error if non-empty\n293: \n294: 2. **Create Directory Handler**\n295:    - JSON bind `CreateDirectoryRequest`\n296:    - Sanitize path; `parseFileMode` (default 0755)\n297:    - `os.MkdirAll` for nested creation\n298:    - Return `CreateDirectoryResponse`\n299: \n300: 3. **Copy Handler**\n301:    - Sanitize source and dest\n302:    - `os.Stat` source; detect file vs dir\n303:    - File: `os.Open` + `io.Copy`\n304:    - Directory: `filepath.Walk` with recursive copy\n305: \n306: 4. **Move Handler**\n307:    - Sanitize source and dest\n308:    - `os.Rename`; handle cross-fs error\n309:    - Return `MoveResponse`\n310: \n311: 5. **Modify Permissions Handler**\n312:    - Wildcard path; JSON body for mode\n313:    - `os.Stat` to get old mode\n314:    - `parseFileMode` for new mode\n315:    - `os.Chmod`; return old/new modes\n316: \n317: 6. **Archive Handler** (new file)\n318:    - Sanitize source and dest paths\n319:    - Detect format from request/extension\n320:    - `tar.Create` or `zip.Create`\n321:    - Walk source; add entries with relative paths\n322:    - Close archive; return size\n323: \n324: 7. **Extract Handler** (new file)\n325:    - Sanitize source; resolve dest (default parent)\n326:    - Open archive; iterate entries\n327:    - For each entry: sanitize entry path; reject escapes\n328:    - Create directories; write files\n329:    - Return extracted file list\n330: \n331: 8. **Route Registration**\n332:    - Add DELETE, POST (directory/copy/move/archive/extract), PATCH routes\n333:    - All under `/api` with existing JWT auth middleware\n334: \n335: 9. **Tests**\n336:    - Delete: file, directory (recursive/non-recursive), non-empty without flag, nonexistent\n337:    - Create directory: single, nested, with mode, already exists\n338:    - Copy: file, directory, nonexistent source, dest exists\n339:    - Move: file, directory, cross-directory, nonexistent source\n340:    - Modify permissions: file, directory, invalid mode, nonexistent\n341:    - Archive: tar, zip, tar.gz, large source, nonexistent source\n342:    - Extract: tar, zip, tar.gz, path escape in archive, large archive rejection\n343: \n344: ## References\n345: \n346: - `code-execution/spec.md` — PicoD base requirements\n347: - `changes/AR-015/proposal.md` — Original PicoD implementation\n348: - `pkg/picod/files.go` — Existing file upload/list/download handlers\n349: - `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` — Path security logic\n350: - [Go archive/tar](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/tar)\n351: - [Go archive/zip](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/zip)\n\n(End of file - total 351 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nExtend PicoD's file management capabilities beyond the basic upload, list, and download operations implemented in AR-015. This adds comprehensive file system manipulation APIs including file deletion, directory creation, file copy/move, permissions modification, and archive operations (tar/zip) for AI agent workspace management.\n\n**Current State**: PicoD (AR-015) provides basic file operations: `POST /api/files` (upload), `GET /api/files?path=...` (list), `GET /api/files/*path` (download). Missing: deletion, directory creation, copy/move, permissions change, and archive handling.\n\n**Target State**: Full-featured file management API suite:\n- `DELETE /api/files/*path` — Delete files and directories\n- `POST /api/files/directory` — Create directories with optional mode\n- `POST /api/files/copy` — Copy files/directories within workspace\n- `POST /api/files/move` — Move/rename files/directories\n- `PATCH /api/files/*path` — Modify file permissions\n- `POST /api/files/archive` — Create tar/zip archives\n- `POST /api/files/extract` — Extract tar/zip archives\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775863134690,"end":1775863134717}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863134721,"sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","part":{"id":"prt_d79b0f1ff001fgALa76D5dk2zD","messageID":"msg_d79b0d931001NUgSrarJDMgXTq","sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-6944cee6204e4d54ba1b510e6f4d282e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-0 |\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: [TO BE FILLED: Define scope of implementation]\n16: \n17: ## Out of Scope\n18: \n19: [TO BE FILLED: Items explicitly out of scope]\n20: \n21: ## Dependencies\n22: \n23: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n24: |------------|---------|---------|\n25: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n26: \n27: ## Deliverables\n28: \n29: | File | Description |\n30: |------|-------------|\n31: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n32: \n33: ## Acceptance Criteria\n34: \n35: - [ ] [TO BE FILLED: Acceptance criteria]\n36: \n37: ## References\n38: \n39: - [TO BE FILLED: Related ARs and documents]\n\n(End of file - total 39 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Define scope of implementation]\n\n## Out of Scope\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Items explicitly out of scope]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/spec.md","time":{"start":1775863134693,"end":1775863134719}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863134723,"sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","part":{"id":"prt_d79b0f98100110YLBmYCUxIX1n","messageID":"msg_d79b0d931001NUgSrarJDMgXTq","sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-9a45160347dd44d3884fd92c7c215adc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Tasks\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Task Checklist\n16: \n17: ### Phase 1: Implementation Verification\n18: \n19: - [ ] **T1.1** Verify `pkg/picod/files.go` structs exist\n20:   - Check: `FileInfo`, `UploadFileRequest`, `FileEntry`, `ListFilesResponse`\n21:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n22:   - Independently verifiable: Structs compile without error\n23: \n24: - [ ] **T1.2** Verify `parseFileMode` function exists\n25:   - Check: Function handles empty, invalid, valid, and >0777 modes\n26:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n27:   - Independently verifiable: Function compiles\n28: \n29: - [ ] **T1.3** Verify `UploadFileHandler` exists\n30:   - Check: Handler supports multipart and JSON/Base64 upload\n31:   - Check: Handler validates path, Base64, mode, creates parent dirs\n32:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n33:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n34: \n35: - [ ] **T1.4** Verify `ListFilesHandler` exists\n36:   - Check: Handler validates path, reads directory, builds FileEntry array\n37:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n38:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n39: \n40: - [ ] **T1.5** Verify `DownloadFileHandler` exists\n41:   - Check: Handler strips leading slash, validates path, detects MIME type\n42:   - Check: Handler sets Content-Disposition header, streams file\n43:   - Verify: `go build ./pkg/picod/`\n44:   - Independently verifiable: Handler compiles\n45: \n46: - [ ] **T1.6** Verify route registration in `pkg/picod/server.go`\n47:   - Check: `/api/files` POST → UploadFileHandler\n48:   - Check: `/api/files` GET → ListFilesHandler\n49:   - Check: `/api/files/*path` GET → DownloadFileHandler\n50:   - Verify: `grep -n \"api.*files\" pkg/picod/server.go`\n51:   - Independently verifiable: All three routes registered\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: ### Phase 2: File Upload Handler Tests\n56: \n57: - [ ] **T2.1** Test multipart upload\n58:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipart` exists and passes\n59:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipart ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n60:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, file written\n61: \n62: - [ ] **T2.2** Test JSON Base64 upload\n63:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerJSON` exists and passes\n64:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerJSON ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n65:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, content decoded\n66: \n67: - [ ] **T2.3** Test invalid Base64 content\n68:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidBase64` exists and passes\n69:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidBase64 ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n70:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid base64 content\"\n71: \n72: - [ ] **T2.4** Test path traversal detection\n73:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n74:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n75:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n76: \n77: - [ ] **T2.5** Test invalid file mode (non-octal)\n78:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidMode` exists and passes\n79:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerInvalidMode ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n80:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, uses default 0644\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T2.6** Test file mode > 0777\n83:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerModeTooHigh` exists and passes\n84:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerModeTooHigh ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n85:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid file mode\"\n86: \n87: - [ ] **T2.7** Test parent directory creation\n88:   - Test: `TestUploadFileHandlerParentDirectoryCreation` exists and passes\n89:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerParentDirectoryCreation ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n90:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, parents created with 0755\n91: \n92: - [ ] **T2.8** Add test for multipart missing path\n93:   - Create: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingPath`\n94:   - Input: multipart form without `path` field\n95:   - Expected: HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\"\n96:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingPath ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n97:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n98: \n99: - [ ] **T2.9** Add test for multipart missing file\n100:   - Create: `TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingFile`\n101:   - Input: multipart form without `file` field\n102:   - Expected: HTTP 400, \"missing file\"\n103:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadFileHandlerMultipartMissingFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n104:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ### Phase 3: File List Handler Tests\n109: \n110: - [ ] **T3.1** Test valid directory listing\n111:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerValidDirectory` exists and passes\n112:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerValidDirectory ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n113:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, FileEntry array\n114: \n115: - [ ] **T3.2** Test missing path parameter\n116:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerMissingPath` exists and passes\n117:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerMissingPath ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n118:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\"\n119: \n120: - [ ] **T3.3** Test path traversal detection\n121:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n122:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n123:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n124: \n125: - [ ] **T3.4** Test non-existent directory\n126:   - Test: `TestListFilesHandlerNonExistent` exists and passes\n127:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerNonExistent ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n128:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 500, \"failed to read directory\"\n129: \n130: - [ ] **T3.5** Add test for empty directory\n131:   - Create: `TestListFilesHandlerEmptyDirectory`\n132:   - Setup: Create empty directory in workspace\n133:   - Expected: HTTP 200, empty `files` array\n134:   - Verify: `go test -run TestListFilesHandlerEmptyDirectory ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n135:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ### Phase 4: File Download Handler Tests\n140: \n141: - [ ] **T4.1** Test existing file download\n142:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerExistingFile` exists and passes\n143:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerExistingFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n144:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, file content matches\n145: \n146: - [ ] **T4.2** Test leading slash stripped\n147:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerLeadingSlash` exists and passes\n148:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerLeadingSlash ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n149:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 200, resolved correctly\n150: \n151: - [ ] **T4.3** Test path traversal detection\n152:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerPathEscape` exists and passes\n153:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerPathEscape ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n154:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"invalid path\"\n155: \n156: - [ ] **T4.4** Test file not found\n157:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerNotFound` exists and passes\n158:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerNotFound ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n159:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 404, \"file not found\"\n160: \n161: - [ ] **T4.5** Test path is directory\n162:   - Test: `TestDownloadFileHandlerIsDirectory` exists and passes\n163:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerIsDirectory ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n164:   - Independently verifiable: HTTP 400, \"path is not a file\"\n165: \n166: - [ ] **T4.6** Add test for MIME type detection (.json)\n167:   - Create: `TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeJSON`\n168:   - Setup: Write `data.json` file\n169:   - Expected: HTTP 200, Content-Type: application/json\n170:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeJSON ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n171:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n172: \n173: - [ ] **T4.7** Add test for unknown extension MIME type\n174:   - Create: `TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeUnknown`\n175:   - Setup: Write `data.xyz` file\n176:   - Expected: HTTP 200, Content-Type: application/octet-stream\n177:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerMIMETypeUnknown ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n178:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n179: \n180: - [ ] **T4.8** Add test for symlink inside workspace\n181:   - Create: `TestDownloadFileHandlerSymlinkInsideWorkspace`\n182:   - Setup: Create file, create symlink pointing to file within workspace\n183:   - Expected: HTTP 200, file content from symlink\n184:   - Verify: `go test -run TestDownloadFileHandlerSymlinkInsideWorkspace ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n185:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Phase 5: File Mode Parsing Tests\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T5.1** Test empty mode returns default\n192:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeEmpty` exists and passes\n193:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeEmpty ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n194:   - Independently verifiable: Returns 0644\n195: \n196: - [ ] **T5.2** Test invalid mode returns default\n197:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeInvalid` exists and passes\n198:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeInvalid ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n199:   - Independently verifiable: Returns 0644\n200: \n201: - [ ] **T5.3** Test mode > 0777 returns error\n202:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeTooHigh` exists and passes\n203:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeTooHigh ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n204:   - Independently verifiable: Returns error \"invalid file mode\"\n205: \n206: - [ ] **T5.4** Test valid mode parsing\n207:   - Test: `TestParseFileModeValid` exists and passes\n208:   - Verify: `go test -run TestParseFileModeValid ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n209:   - Independently verifiable: Returns correct FileMode\n210: \n211: ---\n212: \n213: ### Phase 6: Integration Tests\n214: \n215: - [ ] **T6.1** Test full file lifecycle\n216:   - Create: `TestFileLifecycle`\n217:   - Steps: Upload file → List directory → Download file → Verify content\n218:   - Verify: `go test -run TestFileLifecycle ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n219:   - Independently verifiable: All operations succeed, content matches\n220: \n221: - [ ] **T6.2** Test large file upload (near 32 MiB limit)\n222:   - Create: `TestUploadLargeFile`\n223:   - Setup: Generate file ~30 MiB\n224:   - Expected: HTTP 200, file written\n225:   - Verify: `go test -run TestUploadLargeFile ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n226:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes\n227: \n228: - [ ] **T6.3** Test concurrent operations\n229:   - Create: `TestConcurrentFileOperations`\n230:   - Setup: Multiple upload/download requests in parallel\n231:   - Expected: All succeed without race conditions\n232:   - Verify: `go test -race -run TestConcurrentFileOperations ./pkg/picod/ -v`\n233:   - Independently verifiable: Test passes with race detector\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### Phase 7: Validation and Linting\n238: \n239: - [ ] **T7.1** Run `go vet` on picod package\n240:   - Run: `go vet ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n241:   - Verify: No warnings\n242:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n243: \n244: - [ ] **T7.2** Run `golangci-lint` on picod package\n245:   - Run: `golangci-lint run ./pkg/picod/... ./cmd/picod/...`\n246:   - Verify: No errors\n247:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n248: \n249: - [ ] **T7.3** Run all tests with race detector\n250:   - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -race -v`\n251:   - Verify: All tests pass\n252:   - Independently verifiable: Command exits 0\n253: \n254: - [ ] **T7.4** Verify test coverage ≥ 80%\n255:   - Run: `go test ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n256:   - Run: `go tool cover -func=coverage.out | grep total`\n257:   - Independently verifiable: Coverage ≥ 80%\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ### Phase 8: Binary Validation\n262: \n263: - [ ] **T8.1** Build picod binary\n264:   - Run: `go build -o picod ./cmd/picod/`\n265:   - Verify: Binary exists\n266:   - Independently verifiable: `ls picod`\n267: \n268: - [ ] **T8.2** Run binary with test public key\n269:   - Setup: Generate RSA key pair\n270:   - Setup: Set `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` env var\n271:   - Run: `./picod -port=8080 -workspace=/tmp/test`\n272:   - Call: `/health` endpoint\n273:   - Expected: HTTP 200 response\n274:   - Independently verifiable: Server starts and responds\n275: \n276: - [ ] **T8.3** Test file upload via binary\n277:   - Setup: Server running with valid JWT\n278:   - Call: `POST /api/files` with JSON upload\n279:   - Expected: HTTP 200, FileInfo returned\n280:   - Independently verifiable: File created in workspace\n281: \n282: ---\n283: \n284: ## Acceptance Criteria\n285: \n286: - [ ] `pkg/picod/files.go` contains FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse structs\n287: - [ ] `parseFileMode` handles empty/invalid/valid/>0777 modes correctly\n288: - [ ] `UploadFileHandler` supports multipart and JSON/Base64 upload\n289: - [ ] `UploadFileHandler` validates path, Base64, mode, creates parent directories\n290: - [ ] `ListFilesHandler` validates path, reads directory, returns FileEntry array\n291: - [ ] `DownloadFileHandler` validates path, detects MIME type, streams file\n292: - [ ] All three file routes registered in server.go\n293: - [ ] All file handler tests pass\n294: - [ ] Path traversal protection works for upload, list, download\n295: - [ ] File mode validation prevents setuid/setgid bits (max 0777)\n296: - [ ] Pass `go vet`\n297: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint`\n298: - [ ] Test coverage ≥ 80%\n299: - [ ] Binary runs with JWT auth and handles file operations\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ## File Changes Summary\n304: \n305: | File | Action | Lines Changed |\n306: |------|--------|---------------|\n307: | `pkg/picod/files.go` | Existing | ~230 lines |\n308: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Existing | Routes at lines 71-73 |\n309: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Modify | +~60 lines (new tests) |\n310: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | Existing | ~35 lines |\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Implementation Notes\n315: \n316: - File upload supports both `multipart/form-data` and `application/json` (Base64 encoded)\n317: - Path sanitization via `sanitizePath` enforces workspace jail security\n318: - File mode parsing: `strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)` for octal, max 0777\n319: - MIME type detection: `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(path))`\n320: - Content-Disposition header: `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"`\n321: - Parent directories created with 0755 mode\n322: - Default file mode: 0644\n\n(End of file - total 322 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Tasks\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Design | [Stage ST-3 completed] |\n\n---\n\n## Task Checklist\n\n### Phase 1: Implementation Verification\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Verify `pkg/picod/files.go` structs exist\n  - Check: `FileInfo`, `UploadFileRequest`, `FileEntry`, `ListFilesResponse`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775863134697,"end":1775863134721}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863134726,"sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","part":{"id":"prt_d79b0f5c0001bpDfE4Euc4RYHX","messageID":"msg_d79b0d931001NUgSrarJDMgXTq","sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5938089c428e4102a0e817bd651103c5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n8: | Module | `pkg/picod` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: PicoD File Management API provides secure file operations within sandbox pods. It exposes REST endpoints for uploading, listing, and downloading files with workspace jail enforcement, path traversal protection, Base64/multipart upload support, and RS256 JWT authentication. The file API enables AI agents and code interpreters to manage workspace files safely within the sandbox boundary.\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Architecture\n18: \n19: ### System Context\n20: \n21: ```\n22: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n23: │                     Kubernetes Cluster                               │\n24: │  ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────┐     ┌─────────────────────────┐│\n25: │  │   Router    │────▶│  Workload   │────▶│      Sandbox Pod        ││\n26: │  │ Deployment  │     │   Manager   │     │ ┌─────────────────────┐ ││\n27: │  │             │     │             │     │ │      PicoD          │ ││\n28: │  │ JWTManager  │     │ Creates     │     │ │  ┌───────────────┐  │ ││\n29: │  │ (Private    │     │ Pod +       │     │ │  │ Files API     │  │ ││\n30: │  │  Key)       │     │ Inject      │     │ │  │               │  │ ││\n31: │  │             │     │ Public Key  │     │ │  │ UploadFile    │  │ ││\n32: │  │             │     │ via Env Var │     │ │  │ ListFiles     │  │ ││\n33: │  │             │     │             │     │ │  │ DownloadFile  │  │ ││\n34: │  │             │     │             │     │ │  └───────────────┘  │ ││\n35: │  │             │     │             │     │ │      Workspace      │ ││\n36: │  │             │     │             │     │ │      (Jail Root)    │ ││\n37: │  └─────────────┘     └─────────────┘     │ └─────────────────────┘ ││\n38: │         │                                 └─────────────────────────┘│\n39: │         │ JWT Token (RS256)                                          │\n40: │         ▼                                                            │\n41: │  ┌─────────────┐                                                    │\n42: │  │   Client    │────▶ Router Proxy ────▶ PicoD /api/files          │\n43: │  │  (SDK/CLI)  │                                                    │\n44: │  └─────────────┘                                                    │\n45: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ### Component Diagram\n49: \n50: ```\n51: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n52: │                         PicoD Server                                 │\n53: │ ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────────┐ │\n54: │ │   Config    │  │   AuthManager   │  │      Gin Engine           │ │\n55: │ │ ┌─────────┐ │  │ ┌─────────────┐ │  │ ┌─────────────────────────┐│ │\n56: │ │ │ Port    │ │  │ │ publicKey   │ │  │ │ Logger Middleware       ││ │\n57: │ │ │Workspace│ │  │ │ mutex       │ │  │ │ Recovery Middleware     ││ │\n58: │ │ └─────────┘ │  │ └─────────────┘ │  │ │ AuthMiddleware          ││ │\n59: │ └─────────────┘  │ AuthMiddleware  │  │ │                         ││ │\n60: │                  │ LoadPublicKey   │  │ │ /api/files (POST/GET)   ││ │\n61: │                  └─────────────────┘  │ │ /api/files/*path (GET)  ││ │\n62: │                                       │ └─────────────────────────┐│ │\n63: │                                       └───────────────────────────┘ │\n64: │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n65: │ │                      sanitizePath                                │ │\n66: │ │   Workspace Jail: symlink resolution, path traversal prevention │ │\n67: │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n68: │ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n69: │ │                   File Operations                                │ │\n70: │ │   Upload: JSON (Base64) or multipart, parent dir creation        │ │\n71: │ │   List:   os.ReadDir with FileEntry metadata extraction          │ │\n72: │ │   Download: MIME type detection, Content-Disposition header      │ │\n73: │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n74: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n75: ```\n76: \n77: ### Request Flow\n78: \n79: ```\n80: File Upload Request:\n81: ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────┐\n82: │  Client  │───▶│  Router  │───▶│            PicoD                  │\n83: │          │    │          │    │                                   │\n84: │ POST     │    │ Validate │    │ 1. AuthMiddleware:                │\n85: │ /api/    │    │ Session  │    │    - Extract Bearer token         │\n86: │ files    │    │ Generate │    │    - Parse JWT with RS256         │\n87: │          │    │ JWT      │    │    - Validate expiration          │\n88: │          │    │          │    │    - Apply MaxBytesReader         │\n89: │          │    │          │    │                                   │\n90: │          │    │          │    │ 2. UploadFileHandler:             │\n91: │          │    │          │    │    - Detect content-type          │\n92: │          │    │          │    │    - Multipart: extract path+file │\n93: │          │    │          │    │    - JSON: decode Base64 content  │\n94: │          │    │          │    │    - sanitizePath(path)           │\n95: │          │    │          │    │    - parseFileMode(mode)          │\n96: │          │    │          │    │    - MkdirAll parent dirs         │\n97: │          │    │          │    │    - WriteFile content            │\n98: │          │    │          │    │    - Return FileInfo              │\n99: └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └───────────────────────────────────┘\n100: \n101: File Download Request:\n102: ┌──────────┐    ┌──────────┐    ┌───────────────────────────────────┐\n103: │  Client  │───▶│  Router  │───▶│            PicoD                  │\n104: │          │    │          │    │                                   │\n105: │ GET      │    │ Validate │    │ 1. AuthMiddleware                 │\n106: │ /api/    │    │ Session  │    │                                   │\n107: │ files/   │    │ Generate │    │ 2. DownloadFileHandler:           │\n108: │ <path>   │    │ JWT      │    │    - Extract wildcard path param  │\n109: │          │    │          │    │    - Trim leading \"/\"             │\n110: │          │    │          │    │    - sanitizePath(path)           │\n111: │          │    │          │    │    - os.Stat (check exists+type)  │\n112: │          │    │          │    │    - MIME type by extension       │\n113: │          │    │          │    │    - Content-Disposition header   │\n114: │          │    │          │    │    - c.File(sanitizedPath)        │\n115: └──────────┘    └──────────┘    └───────────────────────────────────┘\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## Data Structures\n121: \n122: ### FileInfo (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n123: \n124: ```go\n125: type FileInfo struct {\n126:     Path     string    `json:\"path\"`     // Relative path from workspace\n127:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`     // File size in bytes\n128:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`     // File mode as octal string (e.g., \"0644\")\n129:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"` // Last modification time\n130: }\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### UploadFileRequest (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n134: \n135: ```go\n136: type UploadFileRequest struct {\n137:     Path    string `json:\"path\" binding:\"required\"`    // Destination path (relative to workspace)\n138:     Content string `json:\"content\" binding:\"required\"` // Base64-encoded file content\n139:     Mode    string `json:\"mode\"`                       // Optional octal file mode (e.g., \"0755\")\n140: }\n141: ```\n142: \n143: ### FileEntry (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n144: \n145: ```go\n146: type FileEntry struct {\n147:     Name     string    `json:\"name\"`     // Entry name (filename or directory name)\n148:     Size     int64     `json:\"size\"`     // Entry size in bytes\n149:     Modified time.Time `json:\"modified\"` // Last modification time\n150:     Mode     string    `json:\"mode\"`     // Entry mode as octal string\n151:     IsDir    bool      `json:\"is_dir\"`   // Whether entry is a directory\n152: }\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### ListFilesResponse (`pkg/picod/files.go`)\n156: \n157: ```go\n158: type ListFilesResponse struct {\n159:     Files []FileEntry `json:\"files\"` // Array of file/directory entries\n160:     Path  string      `json:\"path\"`  // Directory path (relative to workspace)\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: ### Server (`pkg/picod/server.go`)\n165: \n166: ```go\n167: type Server struct {\n168:     config      *Config               // Server configuration\n169:     engine      *gin.Engine           // Gin HTTP framework\n170:     httpServer  *http.Server          // Underlying HTTP server\n171:     authManager *AuthManager          // JWT authentication manager\n172:     workspace   string                // Resolved workspace directory (absolute path)\n173:     startTime   time.Time             // Server start time for uptime tracking\n174: }\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ### Constants\n178: \n179: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n180: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n181: | `maxFileMode` | `0777` | `files.go` | Maximum file mode permission (prevent setuid/setgid) |\n182: | `defaultFileMode` | `0644` | `files.go` | Default file mode when mode invalid/empty |\n183: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | `auth.go` | Environment variable for PEM public key |\n184: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (32 MiB) | `auth.go` | Request body size limit after JWT validation |\n185: | `version` | `\"0.0.1\"` | `health.go` | PicoD version string |\n186: | `service` | `\"PicoD\"` | `health.go` | Service name for health response |\n187: | `readHeaderTimeout` | `10 * time.Second` | `server.go` | HTTP ReadHeaderTimeout |\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ## API Contracts\n192: \n193: ### Endpoints Summary\n194: \n195: | Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler | Description |\n196: |----------|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n197: | `/health` | GET | No | `HealthCheckHandler` | Server health status |\n198: | `/api/files` | POST | JWT | `UploadFileHandler` | Upload file (multipart or JSON) |\n199: | `/api/files` | GET | JWT | `ListFilesHandler` | List directory contents |\n200: | `/api/files/*path` | GET | JWT | `DownloadFileHandler` | Download file |\n201: \n202: ### Upload File (JSON)\n203: \n204: **Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n205: \n206: **Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n207: \n208: **Content-Type**: `application/json`\n209: \n210: **Request Body**:\n211: ```json\n212: {\n213:     \"path\": \"output/result.txt\",\n214:     \"content\": \"SGVsbG8gV29ybGQ=\",  // Base64-encoded\n215:     \"mode\": \"0644\"\n216: }\n217: ```\n218: \n219: **Request Fields**:\n220: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n221: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n222: | `path` | `string` | Yes | Destination path relative to workspace |\n223: | `content` | `string` | Yes | Base64-encoded file content |\n224: | `mode` | `string` | No | Octal file mode (default: 0644, max: 0777) |\n225: \n226: **Response** (200 OK):\n227: ```json\n228: {\n229:     \"path\": \"output/result.txt\",\n230:     \"size\": 11,\n231:     \"mode\": \"0644\",\n232:     \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T10:35:00Z\"\n233: }\n234: ```\n235: \n236: **Error Responses**:\n237: - 400 Bad Request: Missing path/file, invalid Base64, path escape, invalid mode\n238: - 401 Unauthorized: Missing/invalid/expired JWT\n239: - 500 Internal Server Error: Parent directory creation failure, write failure\n240: \n241: ### Upload File (Multipart)\n242: \n243: **Endpoint**: `POST /api/files`\n244: \n245: **Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n246: \n247: **Content-Type**: `multipart/form-data`\n248: \n249: **Form Fields**:\n250: | Field | Type | Required | Description |\n251: |-------|------|----------|-------------|\n252: | `path` | `string` | Yes | Destination path |\n253: | `file` | `file` | Yes | File content |\n254: | `mode` | `string` | No | Octal file mode |\n255: \n256: **Response** (200 OK): Same as JSON upload\n257: \n258: ### List Files\n259: \n260: **Endpoint**: `GET /api/files?path=<directory>`\n261: \n262: **Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n263: \n264: **Query Parameters**:\n265: | Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n266: |-----------|------|----------|-------------|\n267: | `path` | `string` | Yes | Directory path to list (relative to workspace) |\n268: \n269: **Response** (200 OK):\n270: ```json\n271: {\n272:     \"files\": [\n273:         {\n274:             \"name\": \"src\",\n275:             \"size\": 4096,\n276:             \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T09:00:00Z\",\n277:             \"mode\": \"0755\",\n278:             \"is_dir\": true\n279:         },\n280:         {\n281:             \"name\": \"main.py\",\n282:             \"size\": 1024,\n283:             \"modified\": \"2026-04-11T10:00:00Z\",\n284:             \"mode\": \"0644\",\n285:             \"is_dir\": false\n286:         }\n287:     ],\n288:     \"path\": \"project\"\n289: }\n290: ```\n291: \n292: **Error Responses**:\n293: - 400 Bad Request: Missing path parameter, path traversal detected\n294: - 401 Unauthorized: Missing/invalid/expired JWT\n295: - 500 Internal Server Error: Directory read failure\n296: \n297: ### Download File\n298: \n299: **Endpoint**: `GET /api/files/<path>`\n300: \n301: **Authentication**: JWT Bearer token (RS256)\n302: \n303: **Path Parameter**: File path relative to workspace (wildcard capture `*path`)\n304: \n305: **Response Headers**:\n306: | Header | Value | Description |\n307: |--------|-------|-------------|\n308: | `Content-Type` | MIME type | Detected from file extension (fallback: `application/octet-stream`) |\n309: | `Content-Disposition` | `attachment; filename=\"<filename>\"` | Download prompt |\n310: \n311: **Response**: File content streamed directly via `c.File(sanitizedPath)`\n312: \n313: **Error Responses**:\n314: - 400 Bad Request: Path traversal detected, path is directory\n315: - 401 Unauthorized: Missing/invalid/expired JWT\n316: - 404 Not Found: File does not exist\n317: - 500 Internal Server Error: Stat failure\n318: \n319: ### Health Check\n320: \n321: **Endpoint**: `GET /health`\n322: \n323: **Authentication**: None (public endpoint)\n324: \n325: **Response** (200 OK):\n326: ```json\n327: {\n328:     \"status\": \"ok\",\n329:     \"service\": \"PicoD\",\n330:     \"version\": \"0.0.1\",\n331:     \"uptime\": \"2h30m15s\"\n332: }\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ## Error Handling\n338: \n339: ### HTTP Status Codes\n340: \n341: | Status | Condition |\n342: |--------|-----------|\n343: | 200 OK | Successful operation |\n344: | 400 Bad Request | Invalid request body, missing required fields, path traversal, invalid Base64, invalid mode, path is directory |\n345: | 401 Unauthorized | Missing Authorization header, invalid JWT, expired token, wrong signing method |\n346: | 404 Not Found | File not found for download |\n347: | 500 Internal Server Error | Directory read failure, file write failure, parent directory creation failure, stat failure |\n348: \n349: ### Error Response Format\n350: \n351: ```json\n352: {\n353:     \"error\": \"<error message>\"\n354: }\n355: ```\n356: \n357: ### Authentication Errors\n358: \n359: | Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n360: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n361: | Missing Authorization header | 401 | `\"missing authorization header\"` |\n362: | Invalid token format | 401 | `\"invalid token format\"` |\n363: | Expired token | 401 | `\"token is expired\"` |\n364: | Non-RSA signing method | 401 | `\"invalid signing method\"` |\n365: | Invalid signature | 401 | `\"invalid signature\"` |\n366: \n367: ### File Upload Errors\n368: \n369: | Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n370: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n371: | Missing path parameter | 400 | `\"missing path parameter\"` |\n372: | Missing file (multipart) | 400 | `\"missing file\"` |\n373: | Invalid request body | 400 | `\"invalid request body\"` |\n374: | Path traversal detected | 400 | `\"invalid path: path escape detected\"` |\n375: | Invalid Base64 content | 400 | `\"invalid base64 content\"` |\n376: | File mode > 0777 | 400 | `\"invalid file mode\"` |\n377: | Parent directory creation failure | 500 | `\"failed to create parent directories\"` |\n378: | File write failure | 500 | `\"failed to write file\"` |\n379: | Stat failure after write | 500 | `\"failed to get file info\"` |\n380: \n381: ### File List Errors\n382: \n383: | Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n384: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n385: | Missing path parameter | 400 | `\"missing path parameter\"` |\n386: | Path traversal detected | 400 | `\"invalid path: path escape detected\"` |\n387: | Directory read failure | 500 | `\"failed to read directory\"` |\n388: \n389: ### File Download Errors\n390: \n391: | Condition | HTTP Status | Error Message |\n392: |-----------|-------------|---------------|\n393: | Path traversal detected | 400 | `\"invalid path: path escape detected\"` |\n394: | Path is directory | 400 | `\"path is not a file\"` |\n395: | File not found | 404 | `\"file not found\"` |\n396: | Stat failure | 500 | `\"failed to stat file\"` |\n397: \n398: ---\n399: \n400: ## Testing Strategy\n401: \n402: ### Unit Tests (`pkg/picod/picod_test.go`)\n403: \n404: #### File Upload Tests\n405: \n406: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n407: |-----------|-------|----------|\n408: | Multipart upload | form-data with path=\"upload.txt\", file content | HTTP 200, FileInfo returned, file written |\n409: | JSON Base64 upload | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"dGVzdCBjb250ZW50\"}` | HTTP 200, FileInfo returned, content decoded |\n410: | Invalid Base64 | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"!!invalid\"}` | HTTP 400, \"invalid base64 content\" |\n411: | Path escape | `{\"path\": \"../escape.txt\", \"content\": \"test\"}` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n412: | Invalid mode (non-octal) | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"test\", \"mode\": \"9999\"}` | HTTP 200, uses default 0644 |\n413: | Mode > 0777 | `{\"path\": \"test.txt\", \"content\": \"test\", \"mode\": \"1000\"}` | HTTP 400, \"invalid file mode\" |\n414: | Parent directory creation | `{\"path\": \"new/dir/file.txt\", \"content\": \"test\"}` | HTTP 200, parents created with 0755 |\n415: | Multipart missing path | form-data without path field | HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\" |\n416: | Multipart missing file | form-data without file field | HTTP 400, \"missing file\" |\n417: | File open failure (multipart) | Invalid form file | HTTP 500, \"failed to open file\" |\n418: | File read failure (multipart) | Read error on form file | HTTP 500, \"failed to read file\" |\n419: \n420: #### File List Tests\n421: \n422: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n423: |-----------|-------|----------|\n424: | List valid directory | `GET /api/files?path=testdir` (with files) | HTTP 200, FileEntry array |\n425: | List empty directory | `GET /api/files?path=emptydir` | HTTP 200, empty files array |\n426: | Missing path parameter | `GET /api/files` | HTTP 400, \"missing path parameter\" |\n427: | Path escape | `GET /api/files?path=../escape` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n428: | Non-existent directory | `GET /api/files?path=nonexistent` | HTTP 500, \"failed to read directory\" |\n429: | Entry info failure | Directory with unreadable entry | Skipped (continue), other entries returned |\n430: \n431: #### File Download Tests\n432: \n433: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n434: |-----------|-------|----------|\n435: | Download existing file | `GET /api/files/testfile.txt` | HTTP 200, file content, correct headers |\n436: | Download with extension | `GET /api/files/data.json` | Content-Type: application/json |\n437: | Unknown extension | `GET /api/files/data.xyz` | Content-Type: application/octet-stream |\n438: | Leading slash stripped | `GET /api/files//absolute.txt` | Resolved correctly |\n439: | Path escape | `GET /api/files/../escape.txt` | HTTP 400, \"invalid path\" |\n440: | File not found | `GET /api/files/nonexistent.txt` | HTTP 404, \"file not found\" |\n441: | Path is directory | `GET /api/files/subdir` | HTTP 400, \"path is not a file\" |\n442: | Symlink inside workspace | Symlink pointing within workspace | Resolved to target file |\n443: \n444: #### Path Sanitization Tests\n445: \n446: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n447: |-----------|-------|----------|\n448: | Valid relative path | `\"subdir/file.txt\"` | Absolute path within workspace |\n449: | Absolute path | `\"/workspace/file.txt\"` | Strips leading `/`, resolves within workspace |\n450: | Path traversal | `\"../escape.txt\"` | Error: path escape detected |\n451: | Deep traversal | `\"subdir/../../escape.txt\"` | Error: path escape detected |\n452: | Existing symlink (safe) | Symlink pointing within workspace | Resolved to target |\n453: | Null byte injection | `\"file\\x00.txt\"` | Cleaned, safe path within workspace |\n454: \n455: #### Authentication Tests\n456: \n457: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n458: |-----------|-------|----------|\n459: | Missing header | No Authorization | HTTP 401, \"missing authorization header\" |\n460: | Invalid format | `Authorization: InvalidFormat` | HTTP 401 |\n461: | Expired token | JWT with expired `exp` | HTTP 401, \"token is expired\" |\n462: | HS256 token | JWT signed with HS256 | HTTP 401, \"invalid signing method\" |\n463: | Valid RS256 token | JWT signed with matching public key | Request proceeds |\n464: \n465: #### File Mode Parsing Tests\n466: \n467: | Test Case | Input | Expected |\n468: |-----------|-------|----------|\n469: | Empty mode | `\"\"` | 0644 (default) |\n470: | Invalid (non-octal) | `\"invalid\"` | 0644 (default) |\n471: | Mode > 0777 | `\"1000\"` | Error: \"invalid file mode\" |\n472: | Valid mode | `\"0755\"` | 0755 |\n473: \n474: ### Test Helper Functions\n475: \n476: ```go\n477: func setupTestServer(t *testing.T) *Server       // Creates test server with temp workspace and RSA key\n478: func generateTestJWT(privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey, expired bool) string  // Generates test JWT token\n479: func makeAuthenticatedRequest(t *testing.T, server *Server, method, path string, body io.Reader, contentType string, jwtToken string) *httptest.ResponseRecorder\n480: func encodePublicKeyPEMForTest(key *rsa.PublicKey) string\n481: ```\n482: \n483: ### Integration Tests\n484: \n485: | Test Scenario | Description |\n486: |---------------|-------------|\n487: | Full file lifecycle | Upload file → List directory → Download file → Verify content matches |\n488: | Auth key mismatch | Router uses different key pair → PicoD rejects token |\n489: | Large file upload | File approaching 32 MiB limit |\n490: | Concurrent operations | Multiple upload/download requests in parallel |\n491: \n492: ---\n493: \n494: ## File Structure\n495: \n496: ```\n497: pkg/picod/\n498: ├── config.go           # Config struct definition (Port, Workspace)\n499: ├── server.go           # Server struct, NewServer, Run, Shutdown, route registration\n500: ├── auth.go             # AuthManager, LoadPublicKeyFromEnv, AuthMiddleware\n501: ├── execute.go          # ExecuteRequest, ExecuteResponse, ExecuteHandler (AR-015)\n502: ├── files.go            # FileInfo, UploadFileRequest, FileEntry, ListFilesResponse, file handlers\n503: ├── health.go           # HealthCheckHandler, version/service constants\n504: ├── sanitize.go         # sanitizePath function for workspace jail security\n505: ├── picod_test.go       # Unit tests for all handlers\n506: └── doc.go              # Package documentation\n507: \n508: cmd/picod/\n509: └── main.go             # Entry point with CLI flag parsing, klog initialization\n510: ```\n511: \n512: ---\n513: \n514: ## Dependencies\n515: \n516: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n517: |---------|---------|---------|\n518: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10+ | HTTP framework, route registration, middleware, JSON binding, multipart form handling |\n519: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2+ | JWT parsing, RSA signing method validation, leeway/expiry options |\n520: | `k8s.io/klog/v2` | Existing | CLI flag registration, structured logging, fatal error handling |\n521: | `crypto/rsa` | Standard | RSA public key type |\n522: | `crypto/x509` | Standard | PKIX public key parsing |\n523: | `encoding/pem` | Standard | PEM block decoding |\n524: | `encoding/base64` | Standard | Base64 decoding for JSON file upload |\n525: | `os` | Standard | File operations: WriteFile, Stat, ReadDir, MkdirAll |\n526: | `path/filepath` | Standard | Path cleaning, symlink resolution, relative path computation, base extraction |\n527: | `mime` | Standard | `mime.TypeByExtension` for download Content-Type |\n528: | `strconv` | Standard | `ParseUint` for octal file mode parsing |\n529: | `strings` | Standard | Path prefix stripping, trimming |\n530: | `time` | Standard | Time handling for FileInfo.Modified |\n531: | `io` | Standard | `io.ReadAll` for multipart file content |\n532: | `mime/multipart` | Standard | Multipart form parsing |\n533: \n534: ---\n535: \n536: ## Implementation Notes\n537: \n538: ### Upload Handler Flow (JSON)\n539: \n540: ```go\n541: func (s *Server) UploadFileHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n542:     contentType := c.ContentType()\n543:     \n544:     // Detect content type\n545:     if contentType == \"multipart/form-data\" {\n546:         // Multipart handling\n547:         path = c.PostForm(\"path\")\n548:         fileHeader, _ := c.FormFile(\"file\")\n549:         file, _ := fileHeader.Open()\n550:         content, _ = io.ReadAll(file)\n551:         modeStr = c.PostForm(\"mode\")\n552:     } else {\n553:         // JSON handling\n554:         var req UploadFileRequest\n555:         c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)\n556:         path = req.Path\n557:         decoded, _ = base64.StdEncoding.DecodeString(req.Content)\n558:         content = decoded\n559:         modeStr = req.Mode\n560:     }\n561:     \n562:     // Sanitize path\n563:     sanitizedPath, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, path)\n564:     \n565:     // Parse file mode\n566:     mode, err := parseFileMode(modeStr)\n567:     \n568:     // Create parent directories\n569:     parentDir := filepath.Dir(sanitizedPath)\n570:     os.MkdirAll(parentDir, 0755)\n571:     \n572:     // Write file\n573:     os.WriteFile(sanitizedPath, content, mode)\n574:     \n575:     // Return FileInfo\n576:     info, _ := os.Stat(sanitizedPath)\n577:     c.JSON(200, FileInfo{...})\n578: }\n579: ```\n580: \n581: ### List Handler Flow\n582: \n583: ```go\n584: func (s *Server) ListFilesHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n585:     path := c.Query(\"path\")\n586:     \n587:     // Sanitize path\n588:     sanitizedPath, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, path)\n589:     \n590:     // Read directory\n591:     entries, err := os.ReadDir(sanitizedPath)\n592:     \n593:     // Build FileEntry array\n594:     files := []FileEntry{}\n595:     for _, entry := range entries {\n596:         info, err := entry.Info()\n597:         if err != nil {\n598:             continue  // Skip entries with stat errors\n599:         }\n600:         files = append(files, FileEntry{\n601:             Name:     entry.Name(),\n602:             Size:     info.Size(),\n603:             Modified: info.ModTime(),\n604:             Mode:     fmt.Sprintf(\"%04o\", info.Mode().Perm()),\n605:             IsDir:    entry.IsDir(),\n606:         })\n607:     }\n608:     \n609:     c.JSON(200, ListFilesResponse{Files: files, Path: path})\n610: }\n611: ```\n612: \n613: ### Download Handler Flow\n614: \n615: ```go\n616: func (s *Server) DownloadFileHandler(c *gin.Context) {\n617:     reqPath := c.Param(\"path\")\n618:     reqPath = strings.TrimPrefix(reqPath, \"/\")\n619:     \n620:     // Sanitize path\n621:     sanitizedPath, err := sanitizePath(s.workspace, reqPath)\n622:     \n623:     // Check file exists and is not directory\n624:     info, err := os.Stat(sanitizedPath)\n625:     if info.IsDir() {\n626:         c.JSON(400, gin.H{\"error\": \"path is not a file\"})\n627:         return\n628:     }\n629:     \n630:     // Detect MIME type\n631:     contentType := mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(sanitizedPath))\n632:     if contentType == \"\" {\n633:         contentType = \"application/octet-stream\"\n634:     }\n635:     \n636:     // Set headers\n637:     filename := filepath.Base(sanitizedPath)\n638:     c.Header(\"Content-Type\", contentType)\n639:     c.Header(\"Content-Disposition\", fmt.Sprintf(\"attachment; filename=\\\"%s\\\"\", filename))\n640:     \n641:     // Stream file\n642:     c.File(sanitizedPath)\n643: }\n644: ```\n645: \n646: ### File Mode Parsing\n647: \n648: ```go\n649: func parseFileMode(modeStr string) (os.FileMode, error) {\n650:     if modeStr == \"\" {\n651:         return defaultFileMode, nil  // 0644\n652:     }\n653:     \n654:     mode, err := strconv.ParseUint(modeStr, 8, 32)\n655:     if err != nil {\n656:         return defaultFileMode, nil  // Invalid → use default\n657:     }\n658:     \n659:     if mode > maxFileMode {  // 0777\n660:         return 0, errors.New(\"invalid file mode\")\n661:     }\n662:     \n663:     return os.FileMode(mode), nil\n664: }\n665: ```\n666: \n667: **Mode Constraints**:\n668: - Max value: `0777` (prevents setuid/setgid/sticky bits)\n669: - Invalid/non-octal strings fall back to `0644`\n670: - Mode > `0777` returns error (reject request)\n671: \n672: ### Route Registration Pattern\n673: \n674: ```go\n675: func NewServer(config *Config) (*Server, error) {\n676:     // ...\n677:     engine.GET(\"/health\", s.HealthCheckHandler)\n678:     \n679:     api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n680:     api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n681:     {\n682:         api.POST(\"/execute\", s.ExecuteHandler)   // AR-015\n683:         api.POST(\"/files\", s.UploadFileHandler)  // AR-016\n684:         api.GET(\"/files\", s.ListFilesHandler)    // AR-016\n685:         api.GET(\"/files/*path\", s.DownloadFileHandler)  // AR-016\n686:     }\n687:     // ...\n688: }\n689: ```\n690: \n691: ### Path Sanitization Algorithm\n692: \n693: The `sanitizePath` function enforces workspace jail security:\n694: \n695: 1. Resolve workspace directory (follow symlinks to get canonical path)\n696: 2. Clean requested path (`filepath.Clean`)\n697: 3. Strip leading `/` if absolute\n698: 4. Join with workspace root\n699: 5. Check relative path doesn't start with `..` (path traversal)\n700: 6. If path exists, re-validate after symlink resolution\n701: 7. Return resolved, safe absolute path\n702: \n703: ### MIME Type Detection\n704: \n705: Uses `mime.TypeByExtension(filepath.Ext(path))`:\n706: - Common extensions: `.json` → `application/json`, `.txt` → `text/plain`\n707: - Unknown extensions: fallback to `application/octet-stream`\n708: \n709: ---\n710: \n711: ## References\n712: \n713: - `changes/AR-015/design.md` — PicoD Execute API design (shared architecture)\n714: - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for sandbox pod configuration\n715: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` — `AuthModePicoD` constant\n716: - `pkg/router/jwt.go` — Router JWT issuance (key pair generation)\n717: - `pkg/router/errors.go` — Router error types pattern\n718: - `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` — HTTP server lifecycle pattern\n719: - [github.com/gin-gonic/gin](https://github.com/gin-gonic/gin) — Gin framework\n720: - [github.com/golang-jwt/jwt](https://github.com/golang-jwt/jwt) — JWT library\n721: - [Go mime package](https://pkg.go.dev/mime) — MIME type detection\n\n(End of file - total 721 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | M |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nPicoD File Management API provides secure file operations within sandbox pods. It exposes REST endpoints for uploading, listing, and downloading files with workspace jail enforcement, path traversal protection, Base64/multipart upload support, and RS256 JWT authentication. The file API enables AI agents and code interpreters to manage workspace files safely within the sandbox boundary.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/design.md","time":{"start":1775863134695,"end":1775863134723}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775863134741,"sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","part":{"id":"prt_d79b0fa05001J0yxSllFXOiZZx","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d79b0d931001NUgSrarJDMgXTq","sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":19022,"input":3520,"output":281,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15221}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775863138943,"sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","part":{"id":"prt_d79b10a7e001O7glgdICmYwmkU","messageID":"msg_d79b0fa2b00124BpSD178zsSn4","sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863146374,"sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","part":{"id":"prt_d79b123a0001LbwCH2cNcyzcWI","messageID":"msg_d79b0fa2b00124BpSD178zsSn4","sessionID":"ses_2864f4149ffegz7gdPWIBi8KvL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-c7daee3dfccc422696791e848208d2b7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Extend PicoD's file management capabilities with comprehensive file system manipulation APIs including file deletion, directory creation, file copy/move, permissions modification, and archive operations (tar/zip) for AI agent workspace management. This builds upon AR-015's basic file operations (upload, list, download) with additional REST endpoints for full-featured workspace file management.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Delete request/response structures\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define structures for file/directory deletion request and response.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: DeleteRequest struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `DeleteRequest` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` (wildcard path from URL)\n26:   - `Recursive bool` with JSON tag `recursive` (for directory deletion)\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: DeleteResponse struct definition\n29: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n30: - **WHEN** reading the `DeleteResponse` struct\n31: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n32:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n33:   - `Deleted bool` with JSON tag `deleted`\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Delete handler\n38: \n39: The system SHALL implement file/directory deletion handler with recursive support.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler path extraction\n42: - **GIVEN** DELETE request to `/api/files/*path`\n43: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n44: - **THEN** `c.Param(\"path\")` SHALL extract wildcard path\n45: - AND leading `/` SHALL be stripped from path\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler path sanitization\n48: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n49: - **WHEN** processing delete path\n50: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, strippedPath)` SHALL be called\n51: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler file existence check\n54: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n55: - **WHEN** checking path\n56: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n57: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if path not found\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler file deletion\n60: - **GIVEN** path is a regular file\n61: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n62: - **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n63: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `DeleteResponse`\n64: - AND `Deleted` SHALL be `true`\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler directory deletion with recursive flag\n67: - **GIVEN** path is a directory AND `Recursive` is `true`\n68: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n69: - **THEN** `os.RemoveAll(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n70: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `DeleteResponse`\n71: - AND `Deleted` SHALL be `true`\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler directory deletion without recursive flag\n74: - **GIVEN** path is a directory AND `Recursive` is `false`\n75: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n76: - **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n77: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if directory is non-empty\n78: - AND error message SHALL indicate directory is not empty\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: DeleteFileHandler empty directory deletion\n81: - **GIVEN** path is an empty directory AND `Recursive` is `false`\n82: - **WHEN** DeleteFileHandler processes request\n83: - **THEN** `os.Remove(sanitizedPath)` SHALL succeed\n84: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Create directory request/response structures\n89: \n90: The system SHALL define structures for directory creation request and response.\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryRequest struct definition\n93: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n94: - **WHEN** reading the `CreateDirectoryRequest` struct\n95: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n96:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n97:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` (optional octal string)\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryResponse struct definition\n100: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n101: - **WHEN** reading the `CreateDirectoryResponse` struct\n102: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n103:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n104:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode`\n105:   - `Created bool` with JSON tag `created`\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### Requirement: Create directory handler\n110: \n111: The system SHALL implement directory creation handler with nested support.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler request binding\n114: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/directory`\n115: - **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler processes request\n116: - **THEN** `CreateDirectoryRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n117: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler path sanitization\n120: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n121: - **WHEN** processing directory path\n122: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Path)` SHALL be called\n123: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler mode parsing\n126: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n127: - **WHEN** parsing directory mode\n128: - **THEN** `parseFileMode(req.Mode)` SHALL be called\n129: - AND default mode SHALL be `defaultDirMode` (`0755`) if mode empty/invalid\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler nested directory creation\n132: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n133: - **WHEN** creating directory\n134: - **THEN** `os.MkdirAll(sanitizedPath, os.FileMode(mode))` SHALL be called\n135: - AND parent directories SHALL be created if not existing\n136: \n137: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler already exists\n138: - **GIVEN** directory already exists\n139: - **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler processes request\n140: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n141: - AND `Created` SHALL be `false`\n142: - AND existing directory mode SHALL be preserved\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: CreateDirectoryHandler response\n145: - **GIVEN** successful directory creation\n146: - **WHEN** CreateDirectoryHandler completes\n147: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n148: - AND `CreateDirectoryResponse` SHALL include path and mode\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ### Requirement: Copy request/response structures\n153: \n154: The system SHALL define structures for file/directory copy request and response.\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: CopyRequest struct definition\n157: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n158: - **WHEN** reading the `CopyRequest` struct\n159: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n160:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source` and `binding:\"required\"`\n161:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest` and `binding:\"required\"`\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: CopyResponse struct definition\n164: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n165: - **WHEN** reading the `CopyResponse` struct\n166: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n167:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source`\n168:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest`\n169:   - `Copied bool` with JSON tag `copied`\n170: \n171: ---\n172: \n173: ### Requirement: Copy handler\n174: \n175: The system SHALL implement file/directory copy handler with recursive support.\n176: \n177: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler request binding\n178: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/copy`\n179: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n180: - **THEN** `CopyRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n181: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler source sanitization\n184: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n185: - **WHEN** processing source path\n186: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Source)` SHALL be called\n187: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler destination sanitization\n190: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n191: - **WHEN** processing destination path\n192: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Dest)` SHALL be called\n193: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler source existence check\n196: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n197: - **WHEN** checking source path\n198: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n199: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler file copy\n202: - **GIVEN** source is a regular file\n203: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n204: - **THEN** `os.Open(source)` SHALL open source file\n205: - AND `os.Create(dest)` SHALL create destination file\n206: - AND `io.Copy(destFile, srcFile)` SHALL copy content\n207: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `CopyResponse`\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler directory copy\n210: - **GIVEN** source is a directory\n211: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n212: - **THEN** `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL be called\n213: - AND walkFunc SHALL copy each file to destination with relative path\n214: - AND directory structure SHALL be preserved\n215: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler symlink handling\n218: - **GIVEN** source contains symlinks\n219: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n220: - **THEN** symlinks SHALL be skipped OR target SHALL be resolved\n221: - AND symlink escape SHALL be validated via `sanitizePath`\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: CopyFileHandler destination exists\n224: - **GIVEN** destination path already exists\n225: - **WHEN** CopyFileHandler processes request\n226: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n227: - AND error message SHALL indicate destination exists\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ### Requirement: Move request/response structures\n232: \n233: The system SHALL define structures for file/directory move request and response.\n234: \n235: #### Scenario: MoveRequest struct definition\n236: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n237: - **WHEN** reading the `MoveRequest` struct\n238: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n239:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source` and `binding:\"required\"`\n240:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest` and `binding:\"required\"`\n241: \n242: #### Scenario: MoveResponse struct definition\n243: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n244: - **WHEN** reading the `MoveResponse` struct\n245: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n246:   - `Source string` with JSON tag `source`\n247:   - `Dest string` with JSON tag `dest`\n248:   - `Moved bool` with JSON tag `moved`\n249: \n250: ---\n251: \n252: ### Requirement: Move handler\n253: \n254: The system SHALL implement file/directory move/rename handler.\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler request binding\n257: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/move`\n258: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n259: - **THEN** `MoveRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n260: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n261: \n262: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler source sanitization\n263: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n264: - **WHEN** processing source path\n265: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Source)` SHALL be called\n266: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler destination sanitization\n269: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n270: - **WHEN** processing destination path\n271: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.Dest)` SHALL be called\n272: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler source existence check\n275: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n276: - **WHEN** checking source path\n277: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n278: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler rename operation\n281: - **GIVEN** valid source and destination paths\n282: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n283: - **THEN** `os.Rename(sanitizedSource, sanitizedDest)` SHALL be called\n284: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `MoveResponse`\n285: \n286: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler cross-filesystem move\n287: - **GIVEN** source and destination on different filesystems\n288: - **WHEN** `os.Rename` returns cross-device error\n289: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n290: - AND error message SHALL indicate cross-filesystem move not supported\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: MoveFileHandler destination exists\n293: - **GIVEN** destination path already exists\n294: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler processes request\n295: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n296: - AND error message SHALL indicate destination exists\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ### Requirement: Modify permissions request/response structures\n301: \n302: The system SHALL define structures for permissions modification request and response.\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsRequest struct definition\n305: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n306: - **WHEN** reading the `ModifyPermissionsRequest` struct\n307: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n308:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path` (wildcard path from URL)\n309:   - `Mode string` with JSON tag `mode` and `binding:\"required\"` (octal string)\n310: \n311: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsResponse struct definition\n312: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n313: - **WHEN** reading the `ModifyPermissionsResponse` struct\n314: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n315:   - `Path string` with JSON tag `path`\n316:   - `OldMode string` with JSON tag `old_mode`\n317:   - `NewMode string` with JSON tag `new_mode`\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: ### Requirement: Modify permissions handler\n322: \n323: The system SHALL implement file/directory permissions modification handler.\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler path extraction\n326: - **GIVEN** PATCH request to `/api/files/*path`\n327: - **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n328: - **THEN** `c.Param(\"path\")` SHALL extract wildcard path\n329: - AND leading `/` SHALL be stripped from path\n330: \n331: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler request binding\n332: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n333: - **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n334: - **THEN** `ModifyPermissionsRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n335: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n336: \n337: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler path sanitization\n338: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n339: - **WHEN** processing modify path\n340: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, strippedPath)` SHALL be called\n341: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if path escape detected\n342: \n343: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler file existence check\n344: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n345: - **WHEN** checking path\n346: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedPath)` SHALL be called\n347: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if path not found\n348: \n349: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler old mode retrieval\n350: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n351: - **WHEN** getting old permissions\n352: - **THEN** `info.Mode().Perm()` SHALL extract current mode\n353: - AND old mode SHALL be formatted as octal string\n354: \n355: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler mode parsing\n356: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n357: - **WHEN** parsing new mode\n358: - **THEN** `parseFileMode(req.Mode)` SHALL be called\n359: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if mode invalid\n360: - AND mode SHALL be validated against `maxFileMode` (`0777`)\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: ModifyPermissionsHandler chmod operation\n363: - **GIVEN** valid new mode\n364: - **WHEN** ModifyPermissionsHandler processes request\n365: - **THEN** `os.Chmod(sanitizedPath, os.FileMode(newMode))` SHALL be called\n366: - AND HTTP `200` SHALL be returned with `ModifyPermissionsResponse`\n367: - AND response SHALL include old and new modes\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ### Requirement: Archive request/response structures\n372: \n373: The system SHALL define structures for archive creation request and response.\n374: \n375: #### Scenario: ArchiveRequest struct definition\n376: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n377: - **WHEN** reading the `ArchiveRequest` struct\n378: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n379:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n380:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n381:   - `Format string` with JSON tag `format` (optional: \"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\")\n382: \n383: #### Scenario: ArchiveResponse struct definition\n384: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n385: - **WHEN** reading the `ArchiveResponse` struct\n386: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n387:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path`\n388:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path`\n389:   - `Format string` with JSON tag `format`\n390:   - `Size int64` with JSON tag `size`\n391: \n392: ---\n393: \n394: ### Requirement: Archive handler\n395: \n396: The system SHALL implement archive creation handler with tar/zip support.\n397: \n398: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler request binding\n399: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/archive`\n400: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler processes request\n401: - **THEN** `ArchiveRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n402: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n403: \n404: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler source path sanitization\n405: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n406: - **WHEN** processing source path\n407: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.SourcePath)` SHALL be called\n408: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n409: \n410: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler destination path sanitization\n411: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n412: - **WHEN** processing destination path\n413: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.DestPath)` SHALL be called\n414: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n415: \n416: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler source existence check\n417: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n418: - **WHEN** checking source path\n419: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n420: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n421: \n422: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler format detection\n423: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n424: - **WHEN** determining archive format\n425: - **THEN** format SHALL be detected from `req.Format` OR `filepath.Ext(req.DestPath)`\n426: - AND supported formats SHALL be `allowedArchiveFormats` (\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\")\n427: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned for unsupported format\n428: \n429: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler tar creation\n430: - **GIVEN** format is \"tar\" or \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\"\n431: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler creates archive\n432: - **THEN** `tar.Create` SHALL be used with `archive/tar` package\n433: - AND `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL walk source\n434: - AND each entry SHALL be added with relative path\n435: - AND gzip SHALL be applied for \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\" format via `compress/gzip`\n436: \n437: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler zip creation\n438: - **GIVEN** format is \"zip\"\n439: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler creates archive\n440: - **THEN** `zip.Create` SHALL be used with `archive/zip` package\n441: - AND `filepath.Walk(source, walkFunc)` SHALL walk source\n442: - AND each entry SHALL be added with relative path\n443: \n444: #### Scenario: ArchiveHandler response\n445: - **GIVEN** successful archive creation\n446: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler completes\n447: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n448: - AND `ArchiveResponse` SHALL include source path, destination path, format, and size\n449: \n450: ---\n451: \n452: ### Requirement: Extract request/response structures\n453: \n454: The system SHALL define structures for archive extraction request and response.\n455: \n456: #### Scenario: ExtractRequest struct definition\n457: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n458: - **WHEN** reading the `ExtractRequest` struct\n459: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n460:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path` and `binding:\"required\"`\n461:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path` (optional: defaults to parent directory)\n462: \n463: #### Scenario: ExtractResponse struct definition\n464: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n465: - **WHEN** reading the `ExtractResponse` struct\n466: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n467:   - `SourcePath string` with JSON tag `source_path`\n468:   - `DestPath string` with JSON tag `dest_path`\n469:   - `Files []FileEntry` with JSON tag `files` (extracted files list)\n470: \n471: ---\n472: \n473: ### Requirement: Extract handler\n474: \n475: The system SHALL implement archive extraction handler with path escape protection.\n476: \n477: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler request binding\n478: - **GIVEN** POST request to `/api/files/extract`\n479: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler processes request\n480: - **THEN** `ExtractRequest` SHALL be bound via `c.ShouldBindJSON(&req)`\n481: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if binding fails\n482: \n483: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler source path sanitization\n484: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n485: - **WHEN** processing source path\n486: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.SourcePath)` SHALL be called\n487: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if source path escape detected\n488: \n489: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler destination path resolution\n490: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n491: - **WHEN** `req.DestPath` is empty\n492: - **THEN** `filepath.Dir(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be used as destination\n493: - WHEN `req.DestPath` is non-empty\n494: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(s.workspace, req.DestPath)` SHALL be called\n495: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if destination path escape detected\n496: \n497: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler source existence check\n498: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n499: - **WHEN** checking source path\n500: - **THEN** `os.Stat(sanitizedSource)` SHALL be called\n501: - AND HTTP `404` SHALL be returned if source not found\n502: \n503: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler size limit check\n504: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n505: - **WHEN** checking archive size\n506: - **THEN** `os.Stat(source).Size()` SHALL get archive size\n507: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if size > `maxArchiveSize` (`100 << 20`)\n508: - AND error message SHALL indicate archive exceeds size limit\n509: \n510: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler format detection\n511: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n512: - **WHEN** determining archive format\n513: - **THEN** format SHALL be detected from `filepath.Ext(req.SourcePath)`\n514: - AND supported formats SHALL be `allowedArchiveFormats`\n515: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned for unsupported format\n516: \n517: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler tar extraction\n518: - **GIVEN** format is \"tar\" or \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\"\n519: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts archive\n520: - **THEN** `tar.NewReader` SHALL be used with `archive/tar` package\n521: - AND gzip SHALL be decompressed for \"tar.gz\" or \"tgz\" via `compress/gzip`\n522: - AND each entry SHALL be extracted to destination\n523: \n524: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler zip extraction\n525: - **GIVEN** format is \"zip\"\n526: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts archive\n527: - **THEN** `zip.OpenReader` SHALL be used with `archive/zip` package\n528: - AND each entry SHALL be extracted to destination\n529: \n530: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler entry path sanitization\n531: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n532: - **WHEN** extracting each archive entry\n533: - **THEN** `sanitizePath(destination, entry.Name)` SHALL be called for each entry path\n534: - AND HTTP `400` SHALL be returned if entry path escapes workspace\n535: - AND entry path SHALL reject `..` components\n536: \n537: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler directory entry creation\n538: - **GIVEN** archive entry is a directory\n539: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts entry\n540: - **THEN** `os.MkdirAll(entryPath, entry.Mode)` SHALL create directory\n541: - AND nested directories SHALL be created\n542: \n543: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler file entry creation\n544: - **GIVEN** archive entry is a file\n545: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler extracts entry\n546: - **THEN** `os.Create(entryPath)` SHALL create file\n547: - AND entry content SHALL be written via `io.Copy`\n548: - AND file mode SHALL be set via `os.Chmod`\n549: \n550: #### Scenario: ExtractHandler response\n551: - **GIVEN** successful extraction\n552: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler completes\n553: - **THEN** HTTP `200` SHALL be returned\n554: - AND `ExtractResponse` SHALL include source path, destination path, and extracted files list\n555: \n556: ---\n557: \n558: ### Requirement: Route registration extension\n559: \n560: The system SHALL extend route registration with new file management endpoints.\n561: \n562: #### Scenario: New file management routes registration\n563: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/server.go`\n564: - **WHEN** registering routes\n565: - **THEN** `/api/files/*path` SHALL be registered with `DeleteFileHandler` (DELETE)\n566: - AND `/api/files/directory` SHALL be registered with `CreateDirectoryHandler` (POST)\n567: - AND `/api/files/copy` SHALL be registered with `CopyFileHandler` (POST)\n568: - AND `/api/files/move` SHALL be registered with `MoveFileHandler` (POST)\n569: - AND `/api/files/*path` SHALL be registered with `ModifyPermissionsHandler` (PATCH)\n570: - AND `/api/files/archive` SHALL be registered with `ArchiveHandler` (POST)\n571: - AND `/api/files/extract` SHALL be registered with `ExtractHandler` (POST)\n572: - AND all routes SHALL use existing JWT auth middleware\n573: \n574: ---\n575: \n576: ### Requirement: Constants\n577: \n578: The system SHALL define constants for file management behavior configuration.\n579: \n580: #### Scenario: defaultDirMode constant\n581: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/files.go`\n582: - **WHEN** reading constants\n583: - **THEN** `defaultDirMode` SHALL be `0755`\n584: \n585: #### Scenario: maxArchiveSize constant\n586: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n587: - **WHEN** reading constants\n588: - **THEN** `maxArchiveSize` SHALL be `100 << 20` (100 MiB)\n589: \n590: #### Scenario: allowedArchiveFormats constant\n591: - **GIVEN** `pkg/picod/archive.go`\n592: - **WHEN** reading constants\n593: - **THEN** `allowedArchiveFormats` SHALL be `[\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\"]`\n594: \n595: ---\n596: \n597: ### Requirement: Error handling\n598: \n599: The system SHALL handle errors with appropriate HTTP status codes and messages.\n600: \n601: #### Scenario: Delete non-empty directory without recursive error\n602: - **GIVEN** directory is non-empty AND `Recursive` is `false`\n603: - **WHEN** delete fails\n604: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n605: - AND body SHALL indicate directory is not empty\n606: \n607: #### Scenario: Cross-filesystem move error\n608: - **GIVEN** `os.Rename` returns cross-device error\n609: - **WHEN** MoveFileHandler encounters error\n610: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n611: - AND body SHALL indicate cross-filesystem move not supported\n612: \n613: #### Scenario: Archive size exceeded error\n614: - **GIVEN** archive size > `maxArchiveSize`\n615: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler detects size violation\n616: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n617: - AND body SHALL indicate archive exceeds size limit\n618: \n619: #### Scenario: Unsupported archive format error\n620: - **GIVEN** unsupported archive format\n621: - **WHEN** ArchiveHandler or ExtractHandler detects format\n622: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n623: - AND body SHALL indicate unsupported format\n624: \n625: #### Scenario: Archive entry path escape error\n626: - **GIVEN** archive entry path escapes workspace\n627: - **WHEN** ExtractHandler detects path escape\n628: - **THEN** HTTP `400` SHALL be returned\n629: - AND body SHALL indicate invalid entry path\n630: \n631: ---\n632: \n633: ## Constants Summary\n634: \n635: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n636: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n637: | `defaultDirMode` | `0755` | `files.go` | Default directory creation mode |\n638: | `maxArchiveSize` | `100 << 20` | `archive.go` | Maximum archive size for extraction (100 MiB) |\n639: | `allowedArchiveFormats` | `[\"tar\", \"zip\", \"tar.gz\", \"tgz\"]` | `archive.go` | Supported archive formats |\n640: \n641: ---\n642: \n643: ## API Endpoints Summary\n644: \n645: | Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler |\n646: |----------|--------|------|---------|\n647: | `/api/files/*path` | DELETE | JWT | `DeleteFileHandler` |\n648: | `/api/files/directory` | POST | JWT | `CreateDirectoryHandler` |\n649: | `/api/files/copy` | POST | JWT | `CopyFileHandler` |\n650: | `/api/files/move` | POST | JWT | `MoveFileHandler` |\n651: | `/api/files/*path` | PATCH | JWT | `ModifyPermissionsHandler` |\n652: | `/api/files/archive` | POST | JWT | `ArchiveHandler` |\n653: | `/api/files/extract` | POST | JWT | `ExtractHandler` |\n654: \n655: ---\n656: \n657: ## File Changes Summary\n658: \n659: | File | Action | Description |\n660: |------|--------|-------------|\n661: | `pkg/picod/files.go` | Extend | Add `DeleteRequest`, `DeleteResponse`, `CreateDirectoryRequest`, `CreateDirectoryResponse`, `CopyRequest`, `CopyResponse`, `MoveRequest`, `MoveResponse`, `ModifyPermissionsRequest`, `ModifyPermissionsResponse`, and handlers |\n662: | `pkg/picod/archive.go` | Create | `ArchiveRequest`, `ArchiveResponse`, `ExtractRequest`, `ExtractResponse`, `ArchiveHandler`, `ExtractHandler` |\n663: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | Extend | Register new file management routes |\n664: | `pkg/picod/picod_test.go` | Extend | Unit tests for new handlers |\n665: \n666: ---\n667: \n668: ## References\n669: \n670: - `changes/AR-015/delta-spec.md` — Original PicoD implementation\n671: - `pkg/picod/sanitize.go` — Path security logic\n672: - [Go archive/tar](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/tar)\n673: - [Go archive/zip](https://pkg.go.dev/archive/zip)\n674: - [Go compress/gzip](https://pkg.go.dev/compress/gzip)\n\n(End of file - total 674 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-016 — PicoD 文件管理 API\n\n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nExtend PicoD's file management capabilities with comprehensive file system manipulation APIs including file deletion, directory creation, file copy/move, permissions modification, and archive operations (tar/zip) for AI agent workspace management. This builds upon AR-015's basic file operations (upload, list, download) with additional REST endpoints for full-featured workspace file management.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Delete request/response structures\n\nThe system SHALL define structures for file/directory deletion request and response.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-016/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775863146339,"end":1775863146372}}}}
